{{!--
  Maintainer notes (not emitted in G-code):
  - Carvera 4-axis (A-rotary) post — Smoothieware-based firmware.
  - A axis is the rotary axis (rotation around X, Carvera 4th Axis HD attachment).
  - CRITICAL: Uses M2 for program end, NOT M30 — M30 on Smoothieware may delete
    the file from the SD card.
  - Carvera ATC is NOT used in 4-axis mode (rotary attachment occupies the table).
  - Spindle range: 6000–15000 RPM. S value comes from dialect snippet.
  - G4 P2 dwell after spindle start lets the spindle reach commanded RPM.
  - M9 at end turns off coolant/vacuum.
  - Z=0 for rotary work is at the stock CENTER (rotation axis), NOT the surface.
  - Lines starting with ";" are operator-visible comments in output.
  - Template context keys: resources/posts/README.md (PostContext / renderPost).
  - Additional context for 4-axis: axisCount, aAxisRangeDeg, aAxisOrientation.
--}}
; Makera Carvera — 4-Axis Rotary G-code
; Machine: {{machine.name}} — {{machine.id}}
{{#if operationLabel}}; Operation: {{operationLabel}}
{{/if}}; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; SAFETY CHECKLIST:
; [1] Rotary attachment secured to table
; [2] Stock centered in chuck, tailstock engaged
; [3] Stock diameter matches CAM setup (Y dimension)
; [4] Z=0 is at stock CENTER (rotation axis), NOT surface
; [5] A=0 set via controller or G28.3 A0
; [6] Air-cut first: spindle off, Z raised, 10% feed override
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Carvera firmware docs
; and your rotary attachment manual before running on the machine.
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; Compare a short program to a known-good file from Makera CAM.
; See docs/MACHINES.md — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): {{machine.workAreaMm.x}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.y}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.z}}
{{#if machine.aAxisRangeDeg}}; A-axis range: continuous (verify against firmware soft limits)
{{/if}}; Spindle range: {{machine.minSpindleRpm}}–{{machine.maxSpindleRpm}} RPM
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
G21              ; millimeters
G90              ; absolute positioning
G17              ; XY plane
{{#if wcsLine}}; Active work offset — verify fixture zero matches G54–G59 selection
{{wcsLine}}
{{/if}}
; Safe retract, center on rotary axis, and spindle start
G0 Z{{machine.workAreaMm.z}} ; safe Z retract
G0 Y0            ; CRITICAL: center tool on rotation axis (Y must be 0 for 4-axis)
{{spindleOn}}
G4 P2            ; dwell 2s for spindle to reach speed
{{#if inverseTimeFeed}}
; --- Inverse-time feed mode (G93) for continuous rotary axis motion ---
G93              ; inverse-time feed mode ON
{{/if}}
; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
{{#each toolpathLines}}
{{this}}
{{/each}}
; --- end toolpath ---
{{#if inverseTimeFeed}}
G94              ; restore feed-per-minute mode
{{/if}}
; --- End ---
{{spindleOff}}
G0 Z{{machine.workAreaMm.z}} ; retract Z
G0 A0            ; return A to zero
G0 X0 Y0        ; park X, re-center Y on rotation axis
M9               ; coolant/vacuum off
M2               ; program end (NOT M30 — M30 may delete file on Smoothieware)
